---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import testimonials from '../content/testimonials.json';
---
<Layout title="Math Tutoring" description="1-on-1 online math tutoring for high school and university students. UBC Honours Mathematics graduate with 10+ years experience.">
  <div class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Math Tutoring</h1>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="page-content">
      <p>I can help you achieve your academic goals with math!</p>

      <p>I offer online 1-on-1 tutoring for high school and university/college.</p>

      <div style="text-align:center; margin: 1.5rem 0;">
        <img src="/images/headshot.jpg" alt="Cameron Geisler" style="max-width:280px; border-radius:8px;">
      </div>

      <p>I’m a graduate of the Honors Mathematics program at the University of British Columbia, with over 10 years of private tutoring experience.</p>

      <p>My specializations are in:</p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>University prep</strong>: Helping grade 9-12 students get accepted into your top-choice post-secondary program, by boosting your math grade, including IB Math, AP Calculus 12, Pre-calculus 12/11/10, Advanced Functions, Calculus and Vectors, and others.</li>
        <li><strong>Adult students</strong>: Helping returning students pass college math, by rebuilding your confidence and relearning foundational skills, even if you’ve forgotten most of it years ago. I explain math concepts in simple and straightforward language, understandable even if you’re not a math person.</li>
      </ul>

      <p>I can also help you with: University Statistics, Discrete Math, Intro to Mathematical Proof, and other advanced topics (just ask!)</p>

      <p><strong>How we’ll work together:</strong></p>

      <ul>
        <li>We’ll meet online, using Google Meet and a virtual whiteboard.</li>
        <li>I can guide you through practice questions that you are stuck on, confusing concepts, test reviews, etc.</li>
        <li>After each lesson, you’ll get a full summary PDF of what we covered, and a practice worksheet of similar problems (with answers included), so you can reinforce your understanding on your own, and use as a reference to review for exams.</li>
        <li>For university students, I offer full course support: Helping you stay organized with your course, and keeping you accountable for studying, homework deadlines, and exam preparation.</li>
      </ul>

      <p><strong>My rate is from $70-90/hour, depending on course level, availability, and other factors.</strong></p>

      <p><strong>I offer a free 15-30 minute session as an intro consultation</strong>, to understand your academic goals, the details of your situation, and give you an idea of how I do things.</p>

      <p><strong>Use the calendar below to book the best time for you!</strong></p>



